This paper deals with developing robust simulation tools for problems involving multiple mathematical scales, which is a common problem in computational mathematics and engineering. The paper presents new monolithic multi-time-step mixed coupling methods for first-order transient systems, which is a topic that falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also employs the dual Schur domain decomposition technique, which is a common technique in scientific computing (cs.SC). Additionally, the paper deals with solving partial differential equations, which is a topic that falls under computational engineering (cs.CE) and scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper presents numerical simulations to verify the theoretical predictions, which is a topic that falls under computational science (cs.SI) and modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
